IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Maryland State Police- Waterloo Barrack Case Number: 23-MSP-024313 Trooper D. Bassett #7039 The incident was recorded on AXON in-car camera equipment. Certifications: -National Highway Safety Transportation Administration (NHSTA) to conduct Standardized Field Sobriety Test (SFST) -Advanced Roadside Impaired Driving Enforcement (ARIDE) -Certified Preliminary Breath Test (PBT) operator -Certified RADAR LIDAR operator -Advanced Crash Investigation Neighborhood Check: Due to the circumstances, no neighborhood check was conducted. Scene Processing: Photographs of the Toyota Tacoma and the crash scene were taken. All tire markings were measured. Victim/Suspect(s): Hernandez Gomez, Ismael H/M, DOB 05/28/1972 Address: 523 Elmwood Road. Baltimore, Maryland 21206 Phone- Drivers License: Maryland; MD10272451786 margin-left:8px">Employment: N/A Disposition: margin-left:8px">Transported to R. Adams Cowley Shock Trauma in Baltimore. Narrative: On Friday, July 7th, 2023, at approximately 1230 hours, the Maryland State Police Waterloo Barrack received a call for a single vehicle collision on northbound I-95 in the area of Vollmerhausen Road in Savage, Howard County, Maryland. I responded to the scene with TFC. Young #6595. Corporal Lantz #5563 of the Maryland State Police Crash Team also responded to assist. Upon arrival to the scene, we identified the following vehicle: Vehicle 1 2016 Toyota Tacoma margin-bottom:11px">Operator- Hernandez Gomez, Ismael (DOB 05/28/1972) No other vehicles were involved in the collision and no witnesses to the crash remained on scene or were reported. Several citizens stopped to assist Hernandez Gomez shortly after the collision occurred. Hernandez Gomez was in the process of being revived by emergency medical services (EMS), who stated that he originally did not have a pulse when he was removed from the vehicle. He started breathing again after being attended to by EMS. Hernandez Gomez was transported to Shock Trauma where he is still recovering. During the course of the investigation, it was revealed that Hernandez Gomez was driving the Toyota northbound on I-95 in lane 1. The Toyota then drove onto the left shoulder where it came into contact with the guardrail. The Toyotas driver side was in contact with the guardrail for approximately 304 feet. The Toyota then drove off the shoulder into the median and traveled approximately 141 feet before striking a large tree head on. The front of the Toyota suffered heavy damage and all airbags were deployed. All events occurred in Howard County, Maryland.
